{"creationTimestamp":"2025-08-14T18:02:11Z","expression":"0 0 * * *","id":"9ababe08-0b74-4672-bb7c-e7a8227d6d4c","lastUpdatedTimestamp":"2025-08-14T18:02:11Z","name":"my-seed-schedule","properties":{"some-property":"a"},"scanType":"INCREMENTAL","seed":"ac7c5765-bef6-42cc-b519-c75df51ebf3b"}
Usage:
  store [<files>...] [flags]

Examples:
	# Store a seed schedule with the JSON configuration in a file
	discovery ingestion seed-schedule store seed-schedules.json

	# Store a seed schedule with the JSON configuration in the data flag
	discovery ingestion seed-schedule store --data '{"name": "my-seed-schedule","expression": "0 0 * * *","properties": {"some-property": "a"},"seed": "ac7c5765-bef6-42cc-b519-c75df51ebf3b","scanType": "INCREMENTAL"}'

Flags:
      --abort-on-error   aborts the operation if there is an error
  -d, --data string      the JSON with the configurations that will be upserted
  -h, --help             help for store
  -p, --profile string   configuration profile to use (default "default")

